== Eclipse ==
You can [http://www.eclipse.org/downloads/ download Eclipse] and install it on your computer, but eclipse is originaly made for java developement and need additionals plugins to be usefull for C/C++ developpement. 

=== C/C++ Development Tools Plugins ([[en/CDT]]) ===
This plugin is working towards providing a fully functional C and C++ Integrated Development Environment (IDE) for the Eclipse platform. 

;With Eclipse 3.x
* Start Eclipse, go to the Help menu->Software Updates->Find and install. Then add the update site
*:<tt><nowiki>http://update.eclipse.org/tools/cdt/releases/new/</nowiki></tt>
* Check the last version of CDT (currently CDT 2.1.1) and click Next
* Check the two feature shown
* Obey the dialog prompts, and restart Eclipse. That's all there is to it!

=== SubEclipse ===
This plugin adds Subversion integration to the Eclipse IDE.

;With Eclipse 3.x
* Start Eclipse, go to the Help menu->Software Updates->Find and install. Then add the update site
*:<tt><nowiki>http://subclipse.tigris.org/update</nowiki></tt>
* Obey the dialog prompts, and restart Eclipse. That's all there is to it!


